# Canonical repo and production deploy

## Git remote (source of truth)

- **Production** is built from **`https://github.com/amac84/treewalk-academy.git`** (branch `main`).
- **`origin` should point at that URL.** Do not assume a similarly named repo (e.g. `treewalkacademy-`) is what Cloudflare clones; confirm remotes with `git remote -v` before advising push/PR flows.
- If the user adds a second remote for experiments, name it clearly (e.g. `fork`) and keep **`origin` = `treewalk-academy`** for day-to-day pushes.

## Cloudflare Pages (this project)

- **Root directory:** `app`
- **Build command:** `npm run build`
- **Output directory:** `dist`

If the live site looks stale after a correct deploy, verify the Pages project is connected to **`amac84/treewalk-academy`**, not another repository.

## Feedback bar → Supabase function

- Local and preview builds need **`VITE_FEEDBACK_FUNCTION_URL`** (full URL to `.../functions/v1/create-linear-ticket`) in **`app/.env`** — see **`app/.env.example`**. Vite does not proxy `/functions/v1` to Supabase by default.
- **Production:** set the same variable in **Cloudflare Pages → Environment variables** (and redeploy). Never commit real `.env` secrets.
